Nikon Z7 witj DX 16-50mm:<br />
<br />
//It switches the camera to DX mode, and then gives you the equivalent to 24-75mm. <span style="color: red;">The nice thing is DX mode still fills the viewfinder, unlike with the optical VFs where you get the small box within the larger view.</span>//<br />
<br />
//I took my Z7 into the store today and tried the Z 16-50mm and the Z 50-250mm DX. <span style="color: red;">I couldn't get the lens VR to work at all with either lens on the Z7, nor could I get the IBIS to work on the Z7. In fact, the menu item was greyed out and there was a response something like &quot;Connect a compatible lens to the camera&quot;</span>--I can't recall the exact response, The VR on both lenses worked fine on the Z50.//

